<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by kitsinu on 03-01-2000 08:04 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I hope that they add some stuff for Gnomes and Dark Elves first.  Gnomes have a max base Wisdom of 102 I think, and are very weak when it comes to the armor.  My biggest complaint about Erudites isn’t their base Wisdom, it is their relative weakness added in.  They are as weak as a Gnome, and have to wear Medium.  The Cleric armor that is so heavy is still lighter than medium plate, so the Erudites and Humans already had a little relief.

I would hope that Dark Elves would have some quests that they could do at all though.  Verant has taken a giant leap forward with Clerics if they continue adding items to the different races.  Give Dwarves something for their Battle Cleric lifestyle (hehe).  Give High Elves something appropriate to their more serene outlook.  Give Gnomes a way of using their Tinkering perhaps.  A weapon that procs at 24 and summons a level 14 tinkered pet with a time limit that only procs when used against something that gives experience?  Base it upon their Tinkering skill (yeah, very expensive to raise high) to give a better pet each level.

What type of items do you think appropriate for your race of Cleric?  So far, Humans and Erudites have : 
1) Light weight stuff that has great AC (without losing much Wisdom if any for the item), 
2) added Magic Resistance, and 
3) a couple of neat effects.  Hopefully, such items will be added to give all the Races their own defining attributes.

Me?  I was happy just getting a veil that would have better AC than a Platinum Ruby veil and an Effect.  Now we learn that we need fear the dark no longer.  It has been tough fighting undead at night when you can't see well.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
